  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DEC Emergency covid response in DRC Beni</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective of this project is to contribute to containing the spread of the Covid-19 pandemic and decrease the morbidity and mortality in target areas. this will be reachable throughout wash, Health and community engagement components. activities will include hygienic kit distribution, awareness campaigns, Covid capacity building to key community actors. 140,000 people are expected to be reached by the awareness campaigns, 7500 pupils within 15 school will benefit, 135 hand washing to be produced, 30,000 mask to produced locally to support local economy, ... Community leaders ( including faith and teachers) to be trained on the covid.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Positive change behaviour of community members toward covid 19 to reduce Morbidity and mortality in the target areas.  Community engagement to be increased, project is developed in the environment that promote accountability, local economy is  restored.</narrative>
  </description>
